{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Smcy1y7C2abEZ6Pkhoy6NF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Prometheus is running on port 9090 internally, but the Service exposes it on port 8000. That's fine.\n\nNow I need to:\n1. Update the Prometheus ConfigMap to add a scrape job for RabbitMQ targeting all 3 pods\n2. Use the pod-specific DNS names via the headless service, or use Kubernetes service discovery\n\nThe simplest approach that uses only native Kubernetes resources and doesn't require CRDs:\n\n**Option 1: Static configs with headless service DNS names**\nThis is the simplest - just list all 3 pod DNS names. Works perfectly for a fixed-size StatefulSet.\nI'm configuring a scrape job that targets each RabbitMQ pod individually using their stable DNS names through the headless service, pointing to the metrics endpoint on port 15692.\n\n**Option 2: Kubernetes service discovery**\nAlternatively, I could use Kubernetes service discovery with label selectors to auto-discover the pods dynamically.\n\nI'm leaning toward Option 1 since it's simpler and doesn't require setting up RBAC rules. Once I update the ConfigMap, I'll need to reload Prometheus's configuration—I can either POST to the `/-/reload` endpoint since the deployment has `--web.enable-lifecycle` enabled, or just restart the pod. Let me verify the port mapping though, since the Service exposes port 8000 but Prometheus typically listens on 9090 internally.\n\nLooking at the startup arguments, there's no explicit `--web.listen-address` flag, so it's using the default 9090. The Service maps 8000 to 9090, so I'll need to use the Service endpoint to trigger the reload. Since both Prometheus and RabbitMQ are in the same namespace, I can use the short DNS form for the RabbitMQ headless service in the Prometheus config.\n\nNow I'll update the ConfigMap to add static configs for all three RabbitMQ pods.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1039,"cache_read_input_tokens":31944,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1039},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"06d8bb8e-3a4c-4ccd-a6c8-2c4a9d1b732e","uuid":"89d34486-8c85-4435-8ed0-7978cdc8bb48","request_id":"req_011CcMRx2NxoRXSNDJtnVZKF"}
