{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EUCX72WqN3251BAF2WQJBS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The targets API only shows 1 active target (prometheus itself) and 0 dropped targets. The RabbitMQ job isn't showing up at all, even though the config file on disk shows the rabbitmq job. \n\nThis is very suspicious. Prometheus completed loading the config after the hot reload, but the RabbitMQ targets aren't appearing. Let me check a couple of things:\n\n1. Maybe the hot reload didn't actually reload the scrape config properly - the logs showed it loaded the file but maybe something is wrong.\n\n2. Let me check if DNS resolution is the issue by testing from the Prometheus pod.\n3. The YAML indentation in the ConfigMap could be wrong and Prometheus might be silently ignoring the rabbitmq job. Looking at the prometheus.yml more carefully, I'm noticing something odd with how the targets are formatted under the rabbitmq job.\n\nThe issue is that `targets:` needs to be either a single-line list with brackets or properly indented as a multi-line list, but I think I may have written it incorrectly in the ConfigMap. Checking the indentation more carefully in the ConfigMap output—the `targets:` key is at 8 spaces, and the list items under it should be at 10 spaces to be properly nested as values of that key, but they're appearing at 8 spaces instead, which makes them look like sibling keys in the same mapping rather than list items under `targets`. I'm working through the YAML indentation to understand how the sequence items under `targets` should be positioned. The child list items need to be indented further than the parent mapping key to be recognized as the value of `targets`, and I'm verifying that the `-` characters for the RabbitMQ entries are at the correct indentation level relative to the `targets:` key.\n\nLet me step back and simplify this by using an inline array format instead to avoid any 